chargeHist.descr: Throw/Discharge Bodily Fluid at Public Safety Worker

result.execSummary:
The defendant Sonya R Wilson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Throw/Discharge Bodily Fluid at Public Safety Worker [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.375(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: $290.60 fine/costs to be paid to the Clerk of Court Office by payment plan of $25.00 per month commencing on January 2, 2017 and the first of each month thereafter until paid in full. Failure to pay will be civil judgment. Bond to be applied.

Must provide DNA sample and pay the $250.00 DNA surcharge to the Clerk of Court Office by payment plan of $25.00 per month commencing on January 2, 2017 and the first of each month thereafter until paid in full. Failure to pay will be civil judgment.   Defendant may request expungement of the DNA sample under Wis. Stat. 165.77(4) by petitioning the Wisconsin Department of Justice. Expungement of DNA is NOT a court process. 
For information see: http://www.doj.state.wi.us/dles/crime-labs/clb-forms.

Must write an apology letter to EMS worker and Emergency Staff, give to District Attorney Office. Must complete a mental health assessment and comply. Must complete an anger management assessment and compliance.

timeConds.notes: Must serve 30 days up front. 150 days banked for use by Probation Agent if necessary. 109 days credit only if revoked. Not subject to good time. Subject to Huber.
